{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"B\n    \n      Dual-Model Split Architecture (Recommended)\n      Separate API routes for chat vs. autonomous agent. /api/chat handles conversational interactions via Qwen with tool-calling (scene control, data queries). /api/agent is the autonomous Claude-powered analyst that runs on schedule, publishes threat assessments, and generates scene annotations. They share a common data layer but are independently deployable.\n      \n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            Each path optimized for its model & use case\n            Chat stays fast (no routing overhead)\n            Autonomous agent can evolve independently\n            Clear separation of concerns — great CV talking point\n            If one model is down, the other still works\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            Two integration paths to maintain\n            Need shared context layer for cross-model awareness","choice":"b","id":null,"timestamp":1775498189012}
